                <pb facs="0377" n="348" xml:id="pg_348"/>
                <p>—Soviet advantage in number of missiles and bombers balanced by U.S. advantage in
                    MIRVed launchers.</p>
                <p>—Soviets retain large throw weight advantage, but most throw weight is in
                    unMIRVed missiles.</p>
                <p>—Heavy systems (missiles and bombers) limited to set ceiling on throw weight.</p>
                <p>—Soviets’ MIRVs would include 650 ICBMs and 400 SLBMs; U.S. would have 550 MIRVed
                    ICBMs and 740 SLBMs.</p>
